                  </persName>
            . I am a constable. I was at dinner at two o'clock, I heard the cry of stop thief,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="180909200081"></xptr>I saw the prisoner with the beef under his arm, and several children running after him; I took him in custody. The prisoner told me that he had bought the beef and paid for it, he would bring an action against me for taking him in custody. He had something else in his pocket that he had got in the same way.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had nothing but a bit of bread for three days, I wanted a bit of meat, I told him I would pay him the next day.</p>
